Playing with a toy car's remote control in his doting brother's arms, it is hard to believe that just weeks ago brain tumour patient Ashya King was being treated in intensive care.

Though bearing a faint scar on the back of his head from his brain surgery, the five-year-old was almost unrecognisable as the desperately ill child seen being wheeled into hospital on a stretcher in early September.

The little boy finished a course of pioneering proton bean therapy last month, and last week was seen with his family in Marbella, Spain, as he continues his recovery.

