Ashya and his family were seen at the Marbella High Care Hospital in Spain, where he has been treated since leaving the hospital in Prague, Czech Republic, after undergoing proton therapy.

He looked intently at the remote as he was carried by older brother Naveed; his mother Naghmeh, 45, and father Brett, 51, not far away as they pushed his younger sister in a buggy. 

In August, Ashya was at the centre of an international manhunt after his parents took him out of Southampton General Hospital because they believed NHS treatment would have left him deaf, blind and brain damaged.

