They were traced to Spain where, at the request of the British authorities, they were put in prison and the five-year-old was held in hospital under armed guard with no family members allowed to see him. 

The Kings had planned to sell a holiday home in southern Spain to fund the pioneering treatment which they desperately wanted their son to have, but which was refused by the NHS in England.

However, after a dramatic U-turn in events, they were eventually released from prison without charge and were able to continue their journey to Prague to the Proton Therapy Centre which had agreed to treat Ashya.

